cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about Dialogue Act Recognition (DAR) which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Computational Linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as Conditional Random Field (CRF) and structured attention network, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) research. Hence, cs.AI and cs.LG (Learning) are also likely categories. The paper also deals with memory mechanisms and hierarchical semantic inference, which are related to Semantic Web (SD) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (NE) subfields. Therefore, cs.SD and cs.NE are also possible categories.
